06/12/2010
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Croatian President Ivo Josipovic visits Banja Luka on Monday (December 6th) to receive the Person of the Year award.
The Banja Luka-based daily Nezavisne Novine chose him for his "selfless work on building better and stronger ties between the peoples and countries in the region".
While in BiH, Josipovic will meet with Bosnian officials, Croats living in the country and representatives of the international community.
(HRT, Tanjug, Danas, Radio Free Europe - 06/12/10)
